<task id="R2-002" project="ai-spaarke-ai-workspace-UI-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extend DataGrid framework defaultRecordOpen for formId + Layout 1 unification</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>datagrid,framework,typescript,react,layout-1</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
Implement FR-01, FR-02, FR-03 together in one focused change to the DataGrid framework:

- **FR-01**: Extend the `configjson.rowOpen` TypeScript type to accept optional `formId?: string`. Backward-compatible (existing records without `formId` deserialize identically to today).
- **FR-02**: In `DataGrid.defaultRecordOpen`, when `rowOpen.formId` is present, pass it to `entityFormOptions.formId` on the `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` call.
- **FR-03**: Rewrite the `type !== 'formDialog'` branch (currently `window.open('_blank')`) to also call `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` with Layout 1 standard options. All row-clicks now open as OOB modals at 85% × 85%.

**Modal size standard (binding)**: `width: { value: 85, unit: '%' }, height: { value: 85, unit: '%' }, position: 1`. Use this exact literal in every Layout 1 call.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior TypeScript / React developer familiar with the Spaarke DataGrid framework and Xrm.Navigation Client API.</role>

  <goal>
`src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/DataGrid/DataGrid.tsx` (or its private `defaultRecordOpen`):
- Accepts optional `formId` in `configjson.rowOpen`
- Always calls `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` (never `window.open`)
- Uses 85% × 85% size options
Regression tests for the DataGrid pass; a new test verifies `formId` is honored when supplied.
  </goal>

