  <steps>
    <step>Read the current `DataGrid.tsx` — locate `defaultRecordOpen` (around line 885–919 per audit).</step>
    <step>Locate the TypeScript type for `configjson.rowOpen`. Extend to add `formId?: string`.</step>
    <step>Update `defaultRecordOpen`: if `rowOpen.formId` present, include `formId` in `entityFormOptions` bag.</step>
    <step>Rewrite the fallback branch (`type !== 'formDialog'`) to also call `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` with 85% × 85% Layout 1 options. Delete or comment out the `window.open` call.</step>
    <step>Update existing DataGrid unit tests to reflect new behavior. Add a test: given `rowOpen.formId` set, `navigateTo` is called with that `formId`.</step>
    <step>Verify: `npm run build` in `Spaarke.UI.Components` succeeds; type checks pass.</step>
    <step>Add a code comment near `defaultRecordOpen` citing the R2 unification decision and the 85% × 85% size standard.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>Read · Edit · Bash (npm test, npm build) · Grep</tools>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>`DataGrid.tsx` compiles without type errors.</criterion>
    <criterion>Existing DataGrid tests pass.</criterion>
    <criterion>New test verifies `formId` is passed through to `entityFormOptions`.</criterion>
    <criterion>`window.open` no longer called from `defaultRecordOpen`.</criterion>
    <criterion>Size options literal is `width: { value: 85, unit: '%' }, height: { value: 85, unit: '%' }, position: 1`.</criterion>
    <criterion>Code comment cites the R2 unification decision.</criterion>
    <criterion>Quality gates: code-review + adr-check clean (FULL rigor).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
